  "texts": [
    "The KNN imputation applies on D N um to remove the missing values, as well as fill them in.",
    "KKN transports information from the complete data and fills in the nearest data points of D N um.",
    "The data set after imputation by KNN is expressed as D KNN_N um: Z-score normalization The Z-Score Normalization 26 is a standardization method it transforms D KNN_N um data into a standard scale with a mean of 0 and a standard deviation of 1.",
    "This data preprocessing method is important, especially when features with different measurement scales, such as the test scores, percentage of student attendance, and levels of engagement, exist in the data set.",
    "If normalization is not done, the larger value range features may skew the learning of the model, hence making some predictions inaccurate."
